<h1 id="href-intro">1. Introduction</h1>
This document is a specification for web service API integration for external clients. The web service API provides methods for creating shipments, printing parcels, pickup requests, tracking and etc.

To get a test account please send us an e-mail to <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#7d1c0d14530f181a140e090f1c091412133d0e0d18181904531f1a" data-sl-link="registrationLink" data-sl-text="registrationText"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="fe9f8e97d08c9b99978d8a8c9f8a979190be8d8e9b9b9a87d09c99">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>
and provide the following info:

<ul>
<li>Name</li>
<li>Company name</li>
<li>Direct Phone number</li>
</ul>

To get technical support for the integration please send us an e-mail to <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#83e2f3eaadf0f6f3f3ecf1f7c3f0f3e6e6e7faade1e4" data-sl-link="techSupportLink" data-sl-text="techSupportText"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="5c3d2c35722f292c2c332e281c2f2c39393825723e3b">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>
and provide the following info:

<ul>
<li>UserName</li>
<li>Error context (if relevant)</li>
<li>Error message (if relevant)</li>
</ul>
and detailed explanation of the situation you need support for.

<h3 id="href-scope">1.1. Scope</h3>
This document specifies Web Service API used to connect external customers to the core system functionality to create, print or track shipments and parcels, using available courier services with their limitations, additional services and options.

<h3 id="href-terms">1.2. Terms And Conditions</h3>
<ul>
<li>Date data types referred in this document that contains actual dates (without time) should be passed as "yyyy-MM-dd" formatted string in the request. Date responses are in the same format.</li>
<li>Date data types referred in this document as datetime should be passed as "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" formatted string in the request. Datetime responses are in the same format.</li>
<li>Boolean data types referred in this document in url based requests could be passed as "true/false, 1/0, y/n, yes/no" case insensitive values. In JSON fields boolean values allowed are only "true/false".</li>
<li>Response data structures may be changed in the future adding additional fields. Therefore, client applications should be able to accept unknown fields in responses for backward compatibility</li>
<li>Letters in text fields which are not in Windows-1251 encoding (ANSI (Latin) + Cyrillic + some special characters) are transliterated to Latin alphabet in Windows-1251 character encoding table. For more details visit <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows-1251">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows-1251.</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="href-overview">1.3. Overview</h3>
The document specifies communication protocol for integration, which is request/response based over HTTP. Each method provides REST/JSON schema to send requests to the server and receive response in JSON (but not in any case) format.
In addition, each method supports URL GET schema to simplify integrations. This approach is a deviation from standard REST patterns for implementation, but however is identified as easy for integration, well accepted and requested by customers.
<br>
The web service API requires user password authentication for each method. All users have a reference to a single client. Some clients may have contracts which include more than one member (different departments/offices etc).
Depending on his/her permissions, a user is either allowed to work with shipments of these members or not.


<h3 id="href-json-schema">1.4. JSON Schema</h3>
API JSON schema is available for download <a href="https://api.speedy.bg/v1/schema" target="_blank">here</a>

<h3 id="href-examples">1.5. Examples</h3>
<p>Examples can be found <a href="https://services.speedy.bg/api/" target="_blank">here</a></p>

<h3 id="rss_feed">1.6. RSS Feed</h3>
<p><a href="https://services.speedy.bg/api/feed" target="_blank">RSS Feed</a></p>

<h1 id="href-description">2. Overall Description</h1>
BASE_URL=https://api.speedy.bg/v1

<h3 id="href-shipment-service">2.1. Shipment Service</h3>
<span class="spanWebService">Web service URL:</span> BASE_URL/shipment

<h3 id="href-create-shipment-req">2.1.1.1. Create Shipment Request (CreateShipmentRequest)</h3>
<span class="spanMethod">Method:</span> POST<br>
<span class="spanContentType">Content-type:</span> application/json; <span class="spanCharset">charset</span>=utf-8<br>
Input parameters:
<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">CreateShipmentRequest</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>userName</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>User name</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>password</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Password</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>language</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Language ("EN", "BG"). Default is the default system language (BG).</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>clientSystemId</td>
<td>Long</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Client system id</td>
<td>Validated against system register for external customers.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>id</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Shipment id</td>
<td>Shipment ID from provided range. If shipment ID is empty the system will generate and return it in response</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>sender</td>

<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>shipmentsOnly</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>If true - search in shipments only, otherwise in shipment and parcels. Default is true</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>includeReturns</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>If true - search in return shipments also. Default is false</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>fromDateTime</td>
<td>Date
(String in format "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ")</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Pick-up date - from. Up to 6 months before</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>toDateTime</td>
<td>Date
(String in format "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ")</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Pick-up date - to</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h3 id="href-print-resp">2.2.1.2. Print Response (PrintResponse)</h3>

In case the response is a PDF document, the result content type is application/pdf.
<span class="spanContentType">Content-type:</span> application/pdf
And content contains pdf bytes.

In case it is a zpl, the content type is text/plain.
<span class="spanContentType">Content-type:</span>text/plain
And content contains zpl text string.

In case of an error, the content type is application/json.
<span class="spanContentType">Content-type:</span>application/json
And content is a JSON with <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-errors">Error </a>structure.

<h3 id="href-bulk-tracking-data-files-req">2.3.2.1. Bulk Tracking Data Files Request (BulkTrackingDataFilesRequest)</h3>
Bulk tracking data files are json files with file id assigned and contain data in format: <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-tracked-parcel">TrackedParcel</a>[]
A greater file id corresponds to a later file publishing.
This method is used to provide links for downloading published data files with tracking information.
This method requires bulk tracking service enrolment, for which you may contact your key account manager. ;

<br><span class="spanWebService">Web service URL:</span> BASE_URL/track/bulk
<br><span class="spanMethod">Method:</span> POST<br>
<span class="spanContentType">Content-type:</span> application/json; <span class="spanCharset">charset</span>=utf-8<br>

<h3 id="href-find-country-resp">2.5.1.2.2. Find Country Response (FindCountryResponse)</h3>
The countries in return are these that match search criteria in request and ordered by:
<ul>
<li>Exact match is on top, followed by</li>
<li>Country name prefix matches, followed by</li>
<li>Country name contains matches (search term is in the name but not a prefix)</li>
</ul>
The result is limited to 10 records.

<h3 id="href-get-all-countries-resp">2.5.1.3.2. Get All Countries Response (GetAllCountriesResponse)</h3>
See <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-country">Country</a> data structure for additional information.
Response is CSV (comma separated) file int UTF8 encoding. The format is:

<ul>
<li><b>id</b> - ISO country id</li>
<li><b>name</b> - Country name in local language</li>
<li><b>nameEn</b> - Country name in English</li>
<li><b>isoAlpha2</b> - ISO alpha 2 code</li>
<li><b>isoAlpha3</b> - ISO alpha 3 code</li>
<li><b>postCodeFormats</b> - all allowed postcode patterns are separated with comma and the whole value is escaped with quotation marks</li>
<li><b>requireState</b> - flag whether country requires state</li>
<li><b>addressType</b> - address type (1 or 2 - see <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-address">ShipmentAddress</a>) for this country</li>
<li><b>currencyCode</b> - current active currency code used for COD</li>
<li><b>defaultOfficeId</b> - default office id</li>
<li><b>streetTypes</b> - comma separated list of all street types escaped with quotation marks in local language. This value is applicable for addressType 1 only</li>
<li><b>streetTypesEn</b> - comma separated list of all street types escaped with quotation marks in English. This value is applicable for addressType 1 only</li>
<li><b>complexTypes</b> - comma separated list of all complex types escaped with quotation marks in local language. This value is applicable for addressType 1 only</li>
<li><b>complexTypesEn</b> - comma separated list of all complex types escaped with quotation marks in English. This value is applicable for addressType 1 only</li>
<li><b>siteNomen</b> - site nomenclature (0, 1 ,2)</li>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>Exact match is on top, followed by</li>
<li>State name prefix matches, followed by</li>
<li>State name contains matches (search term is in the name but not a prefix)</li>
</ul>
The result is limited to 10 records.

<h3 id="href-get-all-sites-resp">2.5.3.3.2. Get All Sites Response (GetAllSitesResponse)</h3>

See <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-site">Site</a> data structure for additional information.
Response is CSV (comma separated) file int UTF8 encoding. The format is:
<ul>
<li><b>id</b> - site id</li>
<li><b>countryId</b> - country id (ISO code)</li>
<li><b>mainSiteId</b> - reference to main site if this site is a "satellite" one</li>
<li><b>type</b> - site type in local language</li>
<li><b>typeEn</b> - site type in English</li>
<li><b>name</b> - site name in local language</li>
<li><b>nameEn</b> - site name in English</li>
<li><b>municipality</b> - municipality in local language</li>
<li><b>municipalityEn</b> - municipality in English</li>
<li><b>region</b> - region in local language</li>
<li><b>regionEn</b> - region in English</li>
<li><b>postCode</b> - default post code for this site (if any)</li>
<li><b>addressNomenclature</b> - code for address nomenclature (streets, complexes, blocks, poi) support. Values are: 0 - no address nomenclature, 1 - partial address nomenclature, 2 - full address nomenclature</li>
<li><b>x</b> - X (longitude) coordinate of site center</li>
<li><b>y</b> - Y (latitude) coordinate of site center</li>
<li><b>servingDays</b> - serving days for this site. Format: 7 serial digits (0 or 1) where each digit corresponds to a day in week (the first digit corresponds to Monday, the second to Tuesday and so on). Value of '0' (zero) means that the site is not served by Speedy on this day while '1' (one) means that it is served. (Example: the text "0100100" means that the site is served on Tuesday and Friday only.)</li>
<li><b>servingOfficeId</b> - Site's serving office</li>
<li><b>servingHubOfficeId</b> - The hub office ID to which serving office is connected</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="href-find-office-resp">2.5.9.2.2. Find Office Response (FindOfficeResponse)</h3>
The offices in return are these that match search criteria in request and ordered by:
<ul class="c92 start">
<li>Exact match is on top, followed by</li>
<li>Office name prefix matches, followed by</li>
<li>Office name contains matches (search term is in the name but not a prefix)</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="href-data-structures">3. Data Structures</h1>
<h3 id="href-ds-shipment-service">3.1. Shipment Service (ShipmentService)</h3>

Shipment service defines service level agreement for the shipment - when shipment should be picked up, service code to be used, sub-services, etc.

<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">ShipmentService</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pickupDate</td>
<td>Date Example: &nbsp;"2017-11-21"</td>
<td>No (default value is today)</td>
<td>The date for shipment pickup.</td>
<td>Could be today or a future date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>autoAdjustPickupDate</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No (default value is false)</td>
<td>To find first available date for pickup starting from pickupDate according to pickup schedule for services</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>serviceId</td>
<td>int</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Service to be used for the shipment.</td>
<td>Service id (code) should be valid for the destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>additionalServices</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-add-services">ShipmentAdditionalServices</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Defines sub-services (like COD, Declared value, etc.) associated with the shipment.</td>
<td>Sub-services may be allowed or forbidden for selected service and/or destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>deferredDays</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No (default value is 0)</td>
<td>This parameter allows users to specify by how many (business) days they would like to postpone the shipment delivery from the standard term.</td>
<td>Allowed values are 0, 1 and 2.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>saturdayDelivery</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>This parameter may adjust delivery date to the first business day, if the standard calculated delivery day is a half-working day. If not specified, system will determine this flag based on configured delivery customer working schedule.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>


<h3 id="href-ds-shipment-add-services">3.1.1. Shipment Additional Services (ShipmentAdditionalServices)</h3>
Allowance of additional services usage in the shipments is controlled and determined by the courier service configuration. All shipment additional services could be either:
<ul>
<li>forbidden for usage with selected courier service</li>
<li>allowed for usage with selected courier service</li>
<li>required for usage with selected courier service</li>
</ul>
Some of the additional services may require additional prerequisites (like valid contracts and annexes or serving offices in pickup or delivery site) to be available for usage.
<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">ShipmentSubServices</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cod</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-add-services-cod">ShipmentCODAdditionalService</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Defines shipment COD sub-service.</td>
<td>Seller could be required to have a valid contract and annex for COD for the destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>obpd</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-add-services-obpd">ShipmentOBPD</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Defines shipment options before payment details.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>declaredValue</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-add-services-ins">ShipmentDeclaredValueAdditionalService</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Defines shipment declared value (extended liability) sub-service.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>fixedTimeDelivery</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>This option fixes the time of delivery on the delivery date. 1130 - means 11:30, 920 - means 09:20</td>
<td>This option is checked against the configured allowed time frame for the service.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>returns</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-add-services-returns">ShipmentReturnAdditionalServices</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Defines a return sub-services.</td>
<td>Return shipments are verified for a return destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>specialDeliveryId</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Specifies special delivery identifier for the shipments. Identifiers are determined in a special delivery annex.</td>
<td>Requires an annex for special delivery.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>deliveryToFloor</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Specifies the floor number in the building where to deliver the shipment.</td>
<td>This sub-service requires an annex.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h3 id="href-ds-shipment-add-services-cod">3.1.1.1. COD Additional Service (ShipmentCODAdditionalService)</h3>
<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">ShipmentCODAdditionalService</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>amount</td>
<td>double</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Defines shipment COD base amount.</td>
<td>Validated against the maximum allowed amounts for the destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>currencyCode</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No (default is the currency code for destination country)</td>
<td>Defines shipment COD currency code.</td>
<td>Validated against the allowed currency code for destination country.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>processingType</td>
<td>enum ["CASH", "POSTAL_MONEY_TRANSFER"]</td>
<td>No (default is "CASH")</td>
<td>Defines COD processing type.</td>
<td>Appropriate contract and annexes may be required.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>payoutToThirdParty</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>If this flag is set, the COD is paid to third party (not to the sender).</td>
<td>Requires a third party to be the payer of the courier service.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>payoutToLoggedClient</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>If this flag is set, the COD is paid to the logged client.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>includeShippingPrice</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Flag indicating whether the shipping price should be included in the COD.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cardPaymentForbidden</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Flag indicating that COD/PMT card payment is forbidden.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>fiscalReceiptItems</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-cod-fiscal-receipt-item">ShipmentCODFiscalReceiptItem</a>[]</td>
<td>This feature depends on country regulations and must be enabled for client contract. The value in amount field is ignored if fiscal receipt items are provided.</td>
<td>List of items to issue fiscal receipt on behalf of client If shipment has fiscal receipt items, the COD amount is the total amount with VAT of all fiscal receipt items.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h3 id="href-ds-shipment-add-services-obpd">3.1.1.4. Options before payment details Additional Service (ShipmentOBPD)</h3>
Options before payment are needed to define what options recipient has on delivery before the payment of the COD. User can open parcels or open and test the content of the parcels. Recipient may accept parcels and pay the COD or refuse to pay and return the parcels. The return shipment details are specified in the options also.

<td>enum["OPEN", "TEST"]</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Defines the option to be used. Open parcels on payment or open and test parcels before payment.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>returnShipmentServiceId</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Defines service id to be used on return.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>returnShipmentPayer</td>
<td>enum ["SENDER", "RECIPIENT", "THIRD_PARTY"]</td>
<td>Yes</td>

<h3 id="href-ds-shipment-content">3.2. Shipment Content (ShipmentContent)</h3>
Shipment content is used to describe what is to be delivered with the shipment.
<table class="tableDataStructure5">

<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">ShipmentContent</td>
</tr>

<td>Constraints</td>

<td>parcelsCount</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Required when parcels list is empty.</td>
<td>Total shipment parcels count. Ignored, if parcels list is not empty. The parcels count is the number of parcels in the lits in that case.</td>
<td>Validated against the minimum and maximum allowed for the service.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>totalWeight</td>
<td>Double</td>

</tr>

<td>Parcels. If omitted a single default (first) parcel will be created for non-pallet and non-postal services. </td>
<td>Validated against the service configuration and pickup and delivery capacity of the depots and couriers.</td>

<tr>
<td>pendingParcels</td>

Pending parcels state is closed with finalizePendingShipment method.</td>

<td></td>

<tr>

<td>Validated against maximum allowed amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<td>An instruction for printing an additional barcode on A6 labels for all parcels. These parameters are used for each generated parcel, unless other instruction provided in the detiled pacel description (<a href="#href-ds-shipment-content-parcel" class="aInternalLink">shipmentParcel</a>).</td>
<td></td>
</tr>

<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-content-parcel-size">ShipmentParcelSize</a></td>
<td>Required for pallet and postal services.</td>
<td>Parcel size (width, height, depth) in cm.</td>
<td>Validated against the capacity of the couriers and depots. Used to calculate the volume weight, if applicable.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>weight</td>
<td>double</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Parcel weight in kg.</td>
<td>Validated against the capacity of the couriers and depots and service configuration.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ref1</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Reference number or text.</td>
<td>20</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ref2</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Reference number or text.</td>
<td>20</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pickupExternalCarrierParcelNumber</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-content-external-carrier-parcel-number">ExternalCarrierParcelNumber</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>External carrier parcel id for pickup</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>deliveryExternalCarrierParcelNumber</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-content-external-carrier-parcel-number">ExternalCarrierParcelNumber</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>External carrier parcel id for delivery</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>goods</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-content-parcel-goods-item">GoodsItem[]</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>For parcels due to customs control. For more information, contact your company representative.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>printAdditionalBarcode</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-parcel-to-print-additional-barcode">ParcelToPrintAdditionalBarcode</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>A custom barcode can be added on A6 labels. This instruction overrides the one provded in the "printAdditionalBarcode" property in the <a href="#href-ds-shipment-content" class="aInternalLink">ShipmentContent</a> structure.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

The declared weight of a parcel (used for price calculation) is the maximum of the weight and the volume weight (calculated from size). Volume weight in some cases is not calculated (for example for pallets).
<a href="https://services.speedy.bg/api/#ParcelsExamples" class="aExamples" target="_blank">View request examples</a>

<h3 id="href-ds-shipment-address">3.4.3. Shipment Address (ShipmentAddress)</h3>
This structure is used to provide addresses. Addresses are two types:
<ul>
<li>Address type 1 (local addresses - currently supported by Romania and Bulgaria)</li>
<li>Address type 2 (foreign addresses - all non-local countries)</li>
</ul>

Address type 1 supports the following requisites:
<ul>
<li>countryId</li>
<li>siteId</li>
<li>siteType</li>
<li>siteName</li>
<li>postCode</li>
<li>complexId</li>
<li>complexType</li>
<li>complexName</li>
<li>streetId</li>
<li>streetType</li>
<li>streetName</li>
<li>streetNo</li>
<li>blockNo</li>
<li>entranceNo</li>
<li>floorNo</li>
<li>apartmentNo</li>
<li>poiId</li>
<li>addressNote</li>
<li>x</li>
<li>y</li>
</ul>

Address type 2 supports the following requisites:
<ul>
<li>countryId</li>
<li>stateId</li>
<li>siteId</li>
<li>siteName</li>
<li>postCode</li>
<li>addressLine1</li>
<li>addressLine2</li>
<li>x</li>
<li>y</li>
</ul>

<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">ShipmentAddress</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>countryId</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No</td>

<td>Validate for valid country code.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>stateId</td>
<td>String</td>

<td>Validate for valid country state.</td>
</tr>

<td>Long</td>

<td>Site id. Used for all address types.</td>
<td>Validate for valid site and value is required.</td>

<td>Max 20</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>siteName</td>
<td>String</td>

<td>Max 50</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<td>String</td>

</tr>
<tr>
<td>streetId</td>
<td>Long</td>

</tr>

<td>streetName</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No. Forbidden, if streetId is provided.</td>
<td>Street name. Used for addresses of type 1 (local address).</td>
<td>Max 50</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>streetNo</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Street number. Used for addresses of type 1 (local address).</td>
<td>Max 10</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>complexId</td>
<td>Long</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Complex identifier. If not provided, but complex type and complex name are provided - the system will try to find unique match by them in site.
Used for addresses of type 1 (local address).</td>
<td>Validate for valid complex.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>complexType</td>
<td>String</td>

<td>Max 15</td>
</tr>

<td>complexName</td>

<td>Max 50</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>blockNo</td>
<td>String</td>

</tr>
<tr>
<td>entranceNo</td>

<td>No</td>
<td>Address note. Used for addresses of type 1 (local address).</td>
<td>200</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>addressLine1</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Required for address type 2.</td>
<td>Address line 1. Used for addresses of type 2 (foreign address).</td>
<td>Max 35</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>addressLine2</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Address line 2. Used for addresses of type 2 (foreign address).</td>
<td>Max 35</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>x</td>
<td>Double</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>GIS coordinates - X .Used for all address types.</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>y</td>
<td>Double</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>GIS coordinates - Y. Used for all address types. </td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

For address type 1, special validation rule is applied:
<ul class="c92 lst-kix_n9je9ydpzox6-0 start">
<li>not empty street (ID or Type&amp;Name) and (streetNo or blockNo) or</li>
<li>not empty complex (ID or Type&amp;Name) and (streetNo or blockNo) or</li>
<li>not empty poiId or</li>
<li>all components of the address within the site stored in addressNote</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://services.speedy.bg/api/#AddressExamples" class="aExamples" target="_blank">View request examples</a>

<h3 id="href-ds-auto-select-nearest-office-policy">3.4.5. Auto-select Nearest Office Policy (AutoSelectNearestOfficePolicy)</h3>
This structure is used to define policy for nearest office auto selection. By default the system tries to find nearest office and if office cannot be determined the shipment is delivered to client address
<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">AutoSelectNearestOfficePolicy</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">

<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>unavailableNearestOfficeAction</td>
<td>enum ["DELIVERY_TO_ADDRESS", "CANCEL_WITH_ERROR"]</td>
<td>No Default is "DELIVERY_TO_ADDRESS"</td>
<td>The action to take if nearest office is unavailable. Values can be:<br><ul><li>"DELIVERY_TO_ADDRESS" - do not change recipient location and deliver to client address</li> <li>"CANCEL_WITH_ERROR" - cancel shipment and return error in response</li></ul></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>officeType</td>
<td>enum ["OFFICE", "APT"]</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Office type filter. Values can be:<br>
<ul>
<li>"OFFICE" - select nearest office</li>
<li>"APT" - select nearest locker (APT)</li>
</ul>
No office filter selection is applied if value is not specified</td>
<td>Not supported for every destination country</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<td>Office same day departure cutoff for days with saturday (HALF) working schedule (departure of parcels delivered to office after the cutoff time is next working day)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>sameDayDepartureCutoffDayOff</td>
<td>String ("HH:mm")</td>
<td>Office same day departure cutoff for non-working days (DAY OFF) working schedule (departure of parcels delivered to office after the cutoff time is next working day)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>maxParcelDimensions</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-content-parcel-size">ShipmentParcelSize</a></td>
<td>Max parcels dimensions for this office</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>maxParcelWeight</td>
<td>double</td>
<td>Max parcel weight</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>type</td>
<td>enum ["OFFICE", "APT"]</td>
<td>Office type</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>nearbyOfficeId</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Nearby office id</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>workingTimeSchedule</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-office-working-time-schedule">OfficeWorkingTimeSchedule</a>[]</td>
<td>Office work time schedule for next days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>palletOffice</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>Pallet office flag</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cardPaymentAllowed</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>Flag, indicating this office allows card payments</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cashPaymentAllowed</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>Flag, indicating this office allows cash payments</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>validFrom</td>
<td>Date (yyyy-MM-dd)</td>
<td>Valid from date</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>validTo</td>
<td>Date (yyyy-MM-dd)</td>
<td>Valid to date</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cargoTypesAllowed</td>
<td>enum[]
(array with values from enum:
["PARCEL", "PALLET", "TYRE"])
(Same as enum in field cargoType in <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-courier-service">CourierService</a>)</td>
<td>Allowed cargo types</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pickUpAllowed</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>Flag, indicating whether parcels can be picked up from office</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>dropOffAllowed</td>
<td>boolean</td>
<td>Flag, indicating whether parcels can be dropped-off in office</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<td>Type</td>
<td>Data</td>
</tr>

<td>date</td>

</tr>

<td>String ("HH:mm")</td>
<td>Office working time start for this date</td>

<tr>

<td>String ("HH:mm")</td>
<td>Office working time end for this date</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<h3 id="href-ds-calculation-service">3.19. Calculation Service</h3>
Calculation service defines service level agreement for the shipment - when shipment should be picked up, service code to be used, sub-services, etc
<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<<td colspan="5">Calculation Service</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>pickupDate</td>
<td>Date<br>(Example: 2017-11-12)</td>
<td>No (default value is today)</td>
<td>The date for shipment pickup.</td>
<td>Could be today or a future date</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>autoAdjustPickupDate</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No (default value is false)</td>
<td>To find first available date for pickup starting from pickupDate according to pickup schedule for services</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>serviceIds</td>
<td>integer[]</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Services for which calculation is requested</td>
<td>Each service id (code) should be valid for the destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>additionalServices</td>
<td><a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-shipment-add-services">ShipmentAdditionalServices</a></td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Defines sub-services (like COD, Declared value, etc.) associated with the shipment.</td>
<td>Sub-services may be allowed or forbidden for selected service and/or destination.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>deferredDays</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No (default value is 0)</td>
<td>This parameter allows users to specify by how many (business) days they would like to postpone the shipment delivery from the standard term.</td>
<td>Allowed values are 0, 1 and 2</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>saturdayDelivery</td>
<td>Boolean</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>This parameter may adjust delivery date to the first business day, if the standard calculated delivery day is a half-working day. If not specified, system will determine this flag based on configured delivery customer working schedule</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h3 id="href-ds-calculation-address-location">3.22. Calculation Address Location</h3>
<table class="tableDataStructure5">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="5">Calculation Address Location</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Data</td>
<td>Constraints</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>countryId</td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Country ISO code. If not provided, local country is assumed. Used for all address types.</td>
<td>Validated for valid country code.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>stateId</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Required, if country supports states</td>
<td>Country state. Used for addresses of type 2 (foreign address).</td>
<td>Validated for valid country state.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>siteId</td>
<td>Long</td>
<td>Required, if country has full site nomenclature and pair (siteType, siteName) is not provided.</td>
<td>Site id. Used for all address types.</td>
<td>Validated for valid site</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>siteType</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Forbidden, if siteId is provided. Otherwise, is not mandatory</td>
<td>Site type can be used in conjunction with countryId and siteName to find unique site. Used for addresses of type 1 (local address).</td>
<td>Max 20 characters</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>siteName</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Forbidden, if siteId is provided. Otherwise, is not mandatory</td>
<td>Site type can be used in conjunction with countryId and siteName to find unique site. Used for all address types.</td>
<td>Max 50 characters</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>postCode</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Required if country requires postcode for addresses</td>
<td>Can be used in conjunction with countryId to find unique site. Used for all address types.</td>
<td>Validated for valid postcode in site and country. Max 10 characters</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<td>totalWeight</td>

</tr>

<h3 id="href-ds-primary-shipment">3.26.6. PrimaryShipment (PrimaryShipment)</h3>
<table class="tableDataStructure3">
<tbody>
<tr class="trTableHeader">
<td colspan="3">PrimaryShipment</td>
</tr>
<tr class="trTableColumnNames">
<td>Name</td>
<td>Type</td>
<td>Data</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>id</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>Primary shipment id</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>type</td>
<td>enum ["RETURN_SHIPMENT", "STORAGE_PAYMENT", "REDIRECT", "SEND_BACK", "MONEY_TRANSFER", "TRANSPORT_DAMAGED", "RETURN_VOUCHER"]</td>
<td>Primary shipment type - how this secondary shipment is related to primary one
<ul>
<li>RETURN_SHIPMENT - if this shipment is one of return of documents (rod) / returnReceipt / swap / return of pallets (rop) for a primary one</li>
<li>STORAGE_PAYMENT - if this shipment is for warehouse charges for a primary one</li>
<li>REDIRECT - if this shipment redirects primary one </li>
<li>SEND_BACK - if this shipment returns primary one to sender</li>
<li>MONEY_TRANSFER - if this shipment is a money transfer for a primary one</li>
<li>TRANSPORT_DAMAGED - if this shipment is for damaged primary shipment transport</li>
<li>VOUCHER_RETURN - if this shipment is a voucher return for a primary one</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

(Same as enum in field type in <a class="aInternalLink" href="#href-ds-primary-shipment">PrimaryShipment</a>)</td>
<td>Primary shipment type - how this secondary shipment is realted to primary one
<ul> <li>RETURN_SHIPMENT - if this shipment is one of return of documents (rod) / returnReceipt / swap / return of pallets (rop) for a primary one</li> <li>STORAGE_PAYMENT - if this shipment is for warehouse charges for a primary one</li> <li>REDIRECT - if this shipment redirects primary one </li> <li>SEND_BACK - if this shipment returns primary one to sender</li> <li>MONEY_TRANSFER - if this shipment is a money transfer for a primary one</li> <li>TRANSPORT_DAMAGED - if this shipment is for damaged primary shipment transport</li> <li>VOUCHER_RETURN - if this shipment is a voucher return for a primary one</li> </ul>
</td>
</tr>
